-- Mol Gains First Day in Five as Oil Rises on China Manufacturing
-- B y   A n d r a s   G e r g e l y
-- 2012-04-02T07:50:52Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-02/mol-gains-first-day-in-five-as-oil-rises-on-china-manufacturing.html
Mol Nyrt. (MOL) ,  Hungary ’s largest
refiner, snapped a four-day losing streak as oil advanced on
signs that the economy is improving in  China , the world’s
second-biggest consumer of crude.  The shares rose as much as 1 percent and last traded 0.3
percent higher at 18,455 forint by 9:42 am. in Budapest. Oil
futures rose as much as 0.5 percent after China’s purchasing
managers’ index climbed to a one-year high in March.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Andras Gergely in Budapest at 
 agergely@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Gavin Serkin at 
